OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FThe recession of 2023 looks shallow,
OL,6,Fit's possible it is already over and
OL,7,Fit may disappear altogether as the
OL,8,FOffice for National Statistics updates
OL,9,Fand revises the data in the months
OL,10,Fahead.
OL,12,FThe more important point is the
OL,13,Feconomy isn't growing and there are
OL,14,Fgood reasons why that's the case.
OL,16,FAs the chancellor pointed out when I
OL,17,Finterviewed him this morning, the
OL,18,Fpainfully high levels of inflation
OL,19,F(not caused by Rishi Sunak) have
OL,20,Fsqueezed the incomes of households.
