OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FBut here's the thing: when it comes to
OL,6,Fliving standards (which is what we
OL,7,Fshould care about most), it's not the
OL,8,Fsize of the economy that matters, it's
OL,9,Fthe amount of growth per person.
OL,11,FGDP per head in the UK (that's the
OL,12,Famount our economy produces, divided
OL,13,Fby all the people in the country) is
OL,14,Fthe key measure that determines how
OL,15,Fmuch our incomes rise over time.
OL,17,FThe terrible news is it has been
OL,18,Ffalling for almost two years.
OL,20,FGDP per head in the U.K. is 1.1% lower
OL,21,Fthan it was before COVID (in Q3 2019).
