OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FBy contrast, over the same period, GDP
OL,6,Fper head has grown by 2.7% in the
OL,7,FEuropean Union and by 6.5% in the
OL,8,FUnited States.
OL,10,FEarlier, I asked the chancellor why we
OL,11,Fare doing so badly.
OL,13,F"UK slips into recession" is a
OL,14,Fpotentially calamitous headline for
OL,15,Fthe government.
OL,17,FThe prime minister has made a
OL,18,Fpolitical pledge and, thus far, he has
OL,19,Ffailed to deliver.
