OL,3,CIs it really 'Rishi's recession'?
OL,5,FEconomically, whether the UK economy
OL,6,Fcontracted or indeed grew slightly at
OL,7,Fthe end of 2023 is almost irrelevant.
OL,9,FWhat matters the most is the UK
OL,10,Feconomy has been stuck in a low-gear
OL,11,Ffor a long time.
OL,13,FAnd, if you look back, living
OL,14,Fstandards have barely improved for the
OL,15,Flast 15 years.
OL,17,FThese are the problems we need our
OL,18,Fpoliticians to fix.
